        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 10:12PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1011 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mabry Mill, or near Willis, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail. Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Floyd...
Willis...
Alum Ridge...
Mabry Mill...
and Rocky Knob Summit.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
